I enjoyed it fine while watching it, but looking at the reviews afterward I have to agree with the points made in the 1 star reviews. The mom wasn't 'missing.' She walked out on her two kids and chose to not make contact again. She was found in a few days and wasn't living far from her parents. She wasn't abducted or anything like that as the title would imply.<br /><br />There is little to no mystery here. It's a feel-good documentary, but it has very little substance.<br /><br />I seriously wonder what awards this could have won.
Not recommended
